itemDescription: English plaintiff in a marriage settlement case; (1691-1788)

wikipedia_page.main: Anne Coventry or Anne Master (21 August 1691 – 21 March 1788) was a litigant over her inheritance.

response: *Gilbert Coventry, 4th Earl of Coventry (d. 1719) (barony extinct), younger brother of second earl (married Anne Coventry).Matthew Kilburn, ‘Coventry , Anne, countess of Coventry (1691–1788)’, Oxford Dictionary of National Biography, Oxford University Press, 2004; online edn, Jan 2008 accessed 28 Nov 2014

Lord Coventry married Elizabeth Allen, daughter of John Allen of Westminster, in 1720. In 1724 he was successfully sued by Anne Coventry, the widow of Gilbert Coventry who was the previous earl, for her inheritance.Matthew Kilburn, 'Coventry , Anne, countess of Coventry (1691–1788)’, Oxford Dictionary of National Biography, Oxford University Press, 2004; online edn, Jan 2008 accessed 28 Nov 2014 He became High Steward of Bridport in 1727.
Anne Coventry, Countess of Coventry may refer to:
* Anne Coventry, Countess of Coventry (1673–1763), British religious writer
* Anne Coventry, Countess of Coventry (1691–1788), litigant over her inheritance
